The paper discusses the use of deep neural networks (DNNs) for molecular property prediction, which falls under the category of machine learning. The paper specifically focuses on uncertainty quantification in DNNs, which is a topic of interest in the subfield of deep learning (cs.LG). The use of graph convolution neural networks (GCNNs) also suggests a potential fit for the computer vision (cs.CV) and natural language processing (cs.CL) subcategories. Additionally, the paper discusses the use of Bayesian inference methods, which is a common technique in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and neural networks (cs.NE).
